<subSubSection pageId="94" pageNumber="2324" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="94.[160,1155,246,340]" pageId="94" pageNumber="2324">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,291,246,271]" italics="true" pageId="94" pageNumber="2324">Etymology.</emphasis>
eması noun in appositionı refers to Emas National Park (Mineirosı Goiásı 
<collectingCountry box="[160,225,282,306]" name="Brazil" pageId="94" pageNumber="2324">Brazil</collectingCountry>
)ı 
<typeStatus box="[241,291,282,306]" pageId="94" pageNumber="2324">type</typeStatus>
locality and where a considerable portion of Cerrado is preserved. This new species is one of the many endemic species of Taquari Plateauı in central 
<collectingCountry box="[990,1053,316,340]" name="Brazil" pageId="94" pageNumber="2324">Brazil</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
